        },
        "body": "+1, this is necessary to publish important lifecycle events for YARN applications. I assume by saying \"flush\" you will actually persist the timeline entity data to the DFS (the entity store), but will not enforce the ATS reader to move them to the summary store, right? ",
        "updateAuthor": {
